Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
ecoOaDesign(25.10)                                          ecoOaDesign(25.10)

Name
       ecoOaDesign  -  Imports  an  OpenAccess  database  and  an ECO-modified
       netlist

Syntax
       ecoOaDesign

       [-help]

       <lib cell view>

       -ecoVerilogFile <input_fileName>

       [-postMask [-<suffix><suffixName>]]

       [-useGACells <GACoreSite>]

       [-reportFile <output_fileName>]

       Imports an OpenAccess database and an  ECO-modified  netlist.  Restores
       the  physical  objects in the database, examines the changes in the new
       netlist, and implements the required connectivity changes in the  logi-
       cal  database  without  making changes to the physical objects. It pre-
       serves the spare cell markings in the old lib/cell/view.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each ecoOaDesign parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man ecoOaDesign.

       <cell> Specifies the OpenAccess cell name of the top cell to import.

       <lib>  Specifies the OpenAccess library name.

       -ecoVerilogFile <input_fileName>
              Specifies the changed Verilog netlist.

              Note: The original netlist must be written out from the original
              <lib  cell view> and it must be hand-modified to incorporate the
              required ECO changes.

       -reportFile <output_fileName>
              Specifies a report file that shows the additions and removals of
              instances and nets in the new Verilog netlist.

              Default: eco.log

       -postMask
              Specifies that ecoOaDesign works in the post-mask mode. If  this
              parameter  is  not specified, then Innovus considers the mode as
              pre-mask by default.

       -<suffix> <suffixName>
              Specifies the suffix name for the the spare cells.

              By default, the suffix is _SPARE.

       <->useGACells<GACoreSite>
              Specifies the GA core site.

              The -useGACells parameter is valid only in the post-mask mode.

              * For cells that match the specified GA core site:

                * Newly added GA cells that exist in memory  but  not  in  the
                  OpenAccess database are left unplaced.

                * GA  cells  that  exist in the OpenAccess database but not in
                  the memory are deleted in the new database.

              * For cells that do not match the specified GA  core  site,  In-
                novus  treats them as standard cells as described in post-mask
                mode.

       <view> Specifies the OpenAccess view name to import.

Examples
       The following command reads the modified Verilog from the  eco.v  file,
       complete  physical  pre-ECO  database  from  the  lib/cell/view design-
       Lib/TOP/final in the post-mask mode:

       ecoOaDesign designLib TOP final -ecoVerilogFile eco.v -postMask

       In post-mask mode, no physical database changes are allowed and the new
       logical changes coming through eco.v are incorporated using spare cells
       in successive ecoPlace and ecoRoute commands.

Related Information
              * ecoPlace

              * ecoRoute

              * For more information, refer to the Innovus-Based ECO Flow sec-
                tion of the Chip Finishing and ECO  Flows  chapter  of   Mixed
                Signal Interoperability Guide.

